Chapter 10 Unsupervised Learning

This notebook is a rough outline of Chapter 10 of An Introduction to Statistical Learning (James et al.(2013)1).

The authors do not provide code for the analysis or figures used throughout each chapter. They do however provide access to some of the data. This notebook uses the data to recreate some of the analysis and figures from the chapter.

Setup

library(ISLR)
library(e1071)
library(ggbiplot)
library(tidyverse)
library(patchwork)
theme_set(theme_bw())

# Given a filename, return the filepath. Default folder is the `data` folder in the current working directory.
get_path <- function(filename) {
  str_c(getwd(), "data", filename, sep = "/")
}

# Colors:
ISLR_blue <- "#176FC0"
ISLR_brown <- "#94340E"
ISLR_lightblue <- "#68A5DB"
ISLR_orange <- "#CC5318"

FIGURE 10.1

The orientation is reversed, but everything else is equal up to a sign flip.

# Perform PCA with scaling:
pr_out1 <- prcomp(USArrests, scale. = TRUE)

# Ref: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/6578355/plotting-pca-biplot-with-ggplot2
ggbiplot(pr_out1, labels =  rownames(USArrests)) +
  ggtitle("FIGURE 10.1")

# Perform PCA without scaling:
pr_out2 <- prcomp(USArrests, scale. = FALSE)

p1 <- ggbiplot(pr_out1) +
  ggtitle("Scaled")
p2 <- ggbiplot(pr_out2) +
  ggtitle("Unscaled")

p1 + p2 + plot_annotation(title = "FIGURE 10.3")

FIGURE 10.4

# Variance and PVE:
pr_out_var <- pr_out1$sdev^2
pr_out_pve <- pr_out_var / sum(pr_out_var)

# Plot:
df <- data.frame("x" = 1:4, "y" = pr_out_pve, "z" = cumsum(pr_out_pve))
p1 <- ggplot(df) +
  geom_path(aes(x, y), color = ISLR_lightblue) +
  geom_point(aes(x, y), color = ISLR_blue) +
  theme_bw() +
  ylim(0, 1) +
  labs(x = "Principal Component",
       y = "Proportion of Variance Explained")

p2 <- ggplot(df) +
  geom_path(aes(x, z), color = ISLR_lightblue) +
  geom_point(aes(x, z), color = ISLR_blue) +
  theme_bw() +
  ylim(0, 1) +
  labs(x = "Principal Component",
       y = "Proportion of Variance Explained")

p1 + p2 + plot_annotation("FIGURE 10.4")

FIGURE 10.15

nci.labs <- NCI60$labs
nci.data <- NCI60$data
pr_out_nci <- prcomp(nci.data, scale = TRUE)

p1 <- ggbiplot(pr_out_nci, var.axes = FALSE, groups = nci.labs, choices = c(1, 2)) +
  theme(legend.position = "none")
p2 <- ggbiplot(pr_out_nci, var.axes = FALSE, groups = nci.labs, choices = c(1, 3)) +
  theme(legend.position = "none")
p1 + p2 + plot_annotation(title = "FIGURE 10.15")

FIGURE 10.16

pr_out_nci_pve <- 100*pr_out_nci$sdev^2 / sum(pr_out_nci$sdev^2)
M <- ncol(pr_out_nci$rotation)
p1 <- tibble(m = 1:M, pve = pr_out_nci_pve) %>% 
  ggplot() +
  geom_path(aes(m, pve), color = ISLR_blue) +
  geom_point(aes(m, pve), color = ISLR_blue,
             alpha = 0.5) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(0, 60, 10)) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0, 10, 2)) +
  labs(x = "Principal Component", y = "PVE")

p2 <- tibble(m = 1:M, pve = pr_out_nci_pve) %>% 
  ggplot() +
  geom_path(aes(m, cumsum(pve)), color = ISLR_orange) +
  geom_point(aes(m, cumsum(pve)), color = ISLR_orange,
             alpha = 0.5) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(0, 60, 10)) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(20, 100, 20)) +
  labs(x = "Principal Component", y = "Cumulative PVE")

p1 + p2 + plot_annotation("FIGURE 10.16")

FIGURE 10.17

This one is done using base R:

sd.data <- scale(nci.data)

par(mfrow = c(3, 1))
data.dist <- dist(sd.data)
plot(hclust(data.dist),
     labels = nci.labs,
     main = "Complete Linkage",
     xlab = "",
     sub = "",
     ylab = "")
plot(hclust(data.dist, method = "average"),
     labels = nci.labs,
     main = "Average Linkage",
     xlab = "",
     sub = "",
     ylab = "")
plot(hclust(data.dist, method = "single"),
     labels = nci.labs,
     main = "Single Linkage",
     xlab = "",
     sub = "",
     ylab = "")
